Some MEPs, however, feared that this would allow insurance companies to "deduct amounts from health insurance".
Thus, doctors will have to buy the products and wait for insurance to reimburse them.
According to estimates, pediatricians will have to individually invest nearly 40,000 crowns per month in vaccines, which is a significant sum.
It will be far from easy, according to Cabrnochov<0xC3><0xA1>.
