Among the few on the right to be unconvinced, a Bush-era hawk, former UN ambassador John Bolton, called the speech "slow, blistered and uninspired" on the National Review Online website.
On the left of the president, Democratic Representative Dennis Kucinich was alarmed that Barack Obama justified the use of force.
When we wrap war in the notion of justice, we can easily justify the slaughter of innocents, he warned.
