Turkish judiciary dissolves pro-Kurdish party, decision with serious consequences
Turkey's Constitutional Court on Friday declared the dissolution of the country's main pro-Kurdish party, a decision that was immediately followed by angry demonstrations in the Kurdish community, in the southeast of the country and in Istanbul.
