Since January, if we add all vehicles that fall into the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, pick-ups, vans, light vans and light chassis trucks) 95,853 have been sold.
The large clouds that affect demand the most have not dissipated, because, although they are also purchased by individuals, most purchases are made by small or medium-sized companies, which pay in almost 100% of cases through external financing.
